<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-9226] Calling super.toString() with @TypeChecked or @CompileStatic will throw java.lang.StackOverflowError</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9226</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following code snippet will throw&#160;java.lang.StackOverflowError:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.transform.CompileStatic
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.transform.TypeChecked

@CompileStatic
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Super {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; toString() { &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;Super&apos;&lt;/span&gt; }
}

@TypeChecked
@CompileStatic
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Child &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; Super {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; toString() { &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;Child &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; &apos;&lt;/span&gt; + &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;super&lt;/span&gt;.toString() }
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// java.lang.StackOverflowError will happen
&lt;/span&gt;println &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Child().toString()&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Any operating systems running Groovy 2.4.x or 2.5.x</environment>
